### Handling missing values

dsSST failed on wrist sensors (LW, RW) for patient `imu0011_visit1`. Since Friedman requires a complete balanced design (no NA) and repeated-measures ANOVA also works best on complete data, **we exclude this sample from all tests involving sensor location**. It is, however, kept in the global FAC analysis (its 3 available sensors still contribute).

```{r anova-na-check}
cadence_cols <- names(df_wide)[startsWith(names(df_wide), "cadence_")]

incomplete <- df_wide %>%
  rowwise() %>%
  mutate(n_ok = sum(!is.na(c_across(all_of(cadence_cols))))) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  filter(n_ok < length(cadence_cols))

if (nrow(incomplete) > 0) {
  cat("Samples with missing sensor data (will be excluded from sensor-effect tests):\n")
  print(incomplete %>% select(sample_id, FAC, all_of(cadence_cols)))
} else {
  cat("No missing values detected.\n")
}

# Build a list of samples to exclude from sensor-effect tests
samples_to_exclude <- incomplete$sample_id
```

